cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on parsing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also heavily relies on pretraining architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a single feed-forward layer to map word vectors to labels, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions analyzing differences across representations for span lengths and dependency displacements, which could potentially relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
